[{"id":"VR852970","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">What is the distance from the shoulder to the center of mass of the arm-hand system?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR852970_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A team of engineers is designing a mechanical arm and hand to be used in a factory assembly line. As shown in the figure, the arm is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.60 meter\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"0.60 meter\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0.60</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></span></span> long with a mass of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1.0 kilogram\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1.0 kilogram\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1.0</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi>kg</mi></math></span></span>, while the hand is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.20 meter\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"0.20 meter\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0.20</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></span></span> long with a mass of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4.0 kilograms\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"4.0 kilograms\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mn>4.0</mn> <mspace width=\"0.2em\"> </mspace> <mi>kg</mi> </math></span></span>. The arm and hand are each assumed to have a uniform density.</p>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of a mechanical arm and hand. The arm, from a point at the left end labeled Shoulder to a point at the right end where it connects to the hand, has a length of 0.60 meter. The hand has a length of 0.20 meter. The arm has a mass of 1.0 kilogram, and the hand has a mass of 4.0 kilograms. A note indicates that the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR852970.g03.svg\" /></div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span ari